# Blog Post Addition Workflow

Every new article requires changes to exactly **6 files**. Always follow this order.

## 1. `lib/content/blog-posts-en.ts`
Append a `BlogPost` object at the end of the array (before `];`):
```ts
{
  title: "Article Title",
  slug: "article-slug",
  metaDescription: "Clean meta description.",
  publishDate: "Feb 20, 2026",
  image: "/blog/tXX.png",
  content: `...full markdown body...`,
}
```

## 2–5. `lib/content/blog-posts-{fr,es,de,pt}.ts`
Append a matching object with:
- Same `slug`, `publishDate`, `image`
- `title` and `content` **fully translated** into the locale language
- Do NOT duplicate English content — the blog page shows a "not translated" banner if `post.content === englishPost.content`

## 6. `lib/blog-post-translations.ts`
Add the slug under each of `fr`, `es`, `de`, `pt` with localized `title` + `metaDescription` (used for blog listings and SEO):
```ts
fr: {
  "article-slug": {
    title: "Translated title",
    metaDescription: "Translated meta.",
  },
},
```

## Copy cleanup rules
- Fix run-on paste artifacts (e.g. `"corerequirement"` → `"core requirement"`)
- Fix missing spaces after punctuation (e.g. `"filler.Here"` → `"filler. Here"`)
- Clean meta description punctuation

## Markdown in content
- `## Heading` — section headings
- `**bold**` — field labels
- `[CTA text →](https://www.typingverified.com/certificate)` — call to action
- `| pipe | tables |` — renders natively via the blog page table handler

## CTA links
- Certificate: `https://www.typingverified.com/certificate`
- Practice test: `https://www.typingverified.com/test`

## Images
- Live in `public/blog/` — confirm the file exists with Glob before using it
- Format: `/blog/tXX.png`

## Verification
Always run `npm run build` at the end and confirm it passes with no TypeScript errors.
